<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 11 at 8:34PM CST  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHWESTERN BOWIE...NORTH
CENTRAL TITUS AND SOUTHERN RED RIVER COUNTIES THROUGH 900 PM CST...
At 834 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Wilkerson, or 10 miles west of Boxelder, moving
northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Boxelder, De Kalb, Talco, Avery, Annona, English, Beaverdams, Harts
Bluff, Lydia, and Cuthand.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
